Don't let my playtime fool you, I've put in somewhere around 900-odd hours into OSRS. I mean it when I say that this game is fun, has a good community, FANTASTIC documentation on its' wiki, and it doesn't take itself too seriously! Even playing with a Free to Play account is a decent way to know what the game's about, but a membership doesn't hurt.

That being said, if you decide this game is for you, *please* consider switching over to the RuneLite client after getting your bearings, it's a third-party client that's been approved by Jagex (You can find a link to it on their website) and makes a world of difference. Even visually, just by changing the render distance and giving you a skybox! I wouldn't have grown to love OSRS without it.
Nostalgia, and little burst of dopamine when leveling up.
